Medical Service Company

Ready for change?

So often caregivers are jumping from agency to agency trying to find the right fit. Do you feel unappreciated? Are you tired of taking care of so many patients without any financial reward?

What would it mean to you to work with an organization that truly cares? What if you only had to work with one client a shift?

 

When you join us you will…



Receive Top Pay In The Area

It’s important that you are properly compensated for your efforts and hard work when caring for those in need.



Have Opportunity For Growth

We want our caregivers to succeed and give them new opportunities to grow within the company.



Be Part Of A Positive Work Environment

Work is so much more rewarding when everyone loves what they do. At Home Nursing is devoted to hiring individuals who know how to have fun, while also getting the job done!



Create Your Own Schedule

Whether you are looking for full-time or part-time work, we offer flexible hours to accommodate your schedule.



Ongoing Training and Support

We take home care seriously and equip all of our caregivers with the training and tools they need.



Make A Difference In The Lives of Seniors

You will be working closely with the senior community who need your care. Once we get to know you, we do our best to pair you with someone we feel you work best with.

Medical Service Company

What is Home care?

Home care is a specialized form of healthcare that provides essential medical and non-medical support to individuals in the comfort of their own homes, enabling them to maintain their independence and receive personalized care.

Your Role – You are responsible for assisting clients with activities of daily living, medication management, mobility support, meal preparation, and companionship. You may also perform light housekeeping tasks, provide transportation, monitor clients’ health, and maintain accurate records of care.

Compassion and effective communication are vital attributes for success in this role.

Excited about California Home Health Care after our caregiver testimonials? Apply for Medical Service Company today!

Apply Now

Medical Service Company benefits

Wait There Is More!

You will also receive…

  • Sign On Bonus
  • 401 K Benefits
  • Swag Bag
  • Appreciation Events
  • Holiday Gifts
  • Opportunity For Referral Bonuses: when you refer a caregiver or client, you earn $250

Here’s what To Expect After You Apply…



We will give you a call to see if it is a right fit



If you decide to join our team, we will schedule you for our 1 day orientation



If there is alignment, then we invite you to the office for an interview



After the completion of orientation, you will be able to choose your shifts

Careers FAQ

How quickly can I start working?

We have clients calling for services every day, so we can usually assign new caregivers once the orientation paperwork and training is completed. 

Do you offer ongoing training?

Yes!  We offer 5 to 12 hours of continuing education every year, and we search for grants so our employees can earn more money just by completing extra voluntary training, when applicable.  

What makes you different from other organizations?

We have a family-like culture, with 10% of our company employees staying with us for longer than a decade, and our average length of service is more than 4 years.  That’s way better than the industry average, because we treat our employees like family. 

Do you pay direct deposit?

Yes!  Most of our employees enjoy free direct deposit every other Friday, right into the accounts of their choosing.  No more hassles of cashing checks or going to the bank! 

Do you offer health benefits?

Yes!  Our full time employees  are eligible for health benefits after 60 days,  including health, vision and dental.  We purchase our benefits through California Choice, meaning employees can choose from dozens of policies to fit their needs.  

Do you offer paid sick time?

Yes!  We follow all state and local laws regarding paid sick time. 

Do you offer a sign on bonus?

We offer a referral bonus for caregivers who refer their friends, family or colleagues who get hired and go to work.  There is no limit to the referrals you can make once you are part of our team, and we pay $200 for each referral. We also give Bonus Bucks each month to our staff just for doing a job well done, and our staff uses those bonus bucks to buy items they want in our company store. 

How long does your staff stay with your team?

As a family company, we make sure our caregivers and nurses feel satisfied with their work.  Through company parties, monthly newsletters and charitable events, we stay in close contact with all of our staff.  As a result, 10% of our workforce has been with us longer than 10 years, and most employees stay at least four years, much better than the industry average.

Excited about California Home Health Care after our caregiver testimonials? Apply for Medical Service Company today!

[Apply Now](https://medicalservicecompany.com/apply-now/)

#### Medical Service Company benefits

## Wait There Is More!

You will also receive…

- Sign On Bonus
- 401 K Benefits
- Swag Bag
- Appreciation Events
- Holiday Gifts
- Opportunity For Referral Bonuses: when you refer a caregiver or client, you earn $250

### Here’s what To Expect After You Apply…



#### We will give you a call to see if it is a right fit



#### If you decide to join our team, we will schedule you for our 1 day orientation



#### If there is alignment, then we invite you to the office for an interview



#### After the completion of orientation, you will be able to choose your shifts

## Careers FAQ

##### How quickly can I start working?

We have clients calling for services every day, so we can usually assign new caregivers once the orientation paperwork and training is completed.

##### Do you offer ongoing training?

Yes!  We offer 5 to 12 hours of continuing education every year, and we search for grants so our employees can earn more money just by completing extra voluntary training, when applicable.

##### What makes you different from other organizations?

We have a family-like culture, with 10% of our company employees staying with us for longer than a decade, and our average length of service is more than 4 years.  That’s way better than the industry average, because we treat our employees like family.

##### Do you pay direct deposit?

Yes!  Most of our employees enjoy free direct deposit every other Friday, right into the accounts of their choosing.  No more hassles of cashing checks or going to the bank!

##### Do you offer health benefits?

Yes!  Our full time employees  are eligible for health benefits after 60 days,  including health, vision and dental.  We purchase our benefits through California Choice, meaning employees can choose from dozens of policies to fit their needs.

##### Do you offer paid sick time?

Yes!  We follow all state and local laws regarding paid sick time.

##### Do you offer a sign on bonus?

We offer a referral bonus for caregivers who refer their friends, family or colleagues who get hired and go to work.  There is no limit to the referrals you can make once you are part of our team, and we pay $200 for each referral. We also give Bonus Bucks each month to our staff just for doing a job well done, and our staff uses those bonus bucks to buy items they want in our company store.

##### How long does your staff stay with your team?

As a family company, we make sure our caregivers and nurses feel satisfied with their work.  Through company parties, monthly newsletters and charitable events, we stay in close contact with all of our staff.  As a result, 10% of our workforce has been with us longer than 10 years, and most employees stay at least four years, much better than the industry average.
